No, only a twinked Beastlord can really outdamage his warder every fight.  Beastlords get dual wield but not double attack meaning they only get three chances at attack per melee round (the third being kick).  <br>
<br>
Just to give you an example:<br>
At level 30, the Beastlord pet double attacks, kicks and bashes.  The pet also gets proc spells which do 30+ dmg an attack.  It hits for 30 and kicks and bashes for around 15.    Meaning that if a pet were to get all successful attacks for full, it would do about 120 damage in one round.  There aren't many weapons that allow a level 30 Beastlord to hit for 60dmg or more per hand.  <br>
<br>
It is possible to outdamage the pet at lower levels, but as the Beastlord gets higher, he becomes less and less able to.  For one thing, the Beastlord can't send the pet in and do damage from far away.  When the Beastlord attacks the mob, it automatically turns on them and ignores the pet, which usually just results in a dead Beastlord (b/c of their low defense skills).  From what I have read, most Beastlords past 39 send their pets in and just keep it healed (which results in a loss of 50% exp per fight).<br>
<br>
---<br>
I do agree though that the exp penalties are a little asinine at this point in the game.  Before Kunark, they were exceptable, because a Magician/Necromancer actually could solo effectively below 50 and often be able to kill faster than other solo classes.  However, post 50, a Magicians effectiveness to solo a mob decreases rendering the penalty as just a penalty and not a balancing factor.<br>
<br>
I never really understood the penalty to begin with, but I think Verant gave more powerful pets which prompted them to add an exp penalty instead of weaker pets so Mages/Necromancers would get exp at the same rate as everyone else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwillansyphus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WillanSyphus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/02 6:46:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Our Pets vs Beastlord Warder Questions...</span><hr size=1> It's been a long time since 30, how much do our pets hit for in a full round? <p>[51 Elementalist] <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90850>Willan Syphus</a> (Gnome)<br>of <a href=http://pub19.ezboard.com/bmithrilvalour>Mithril Valour</a>, on Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalasarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balasarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Italics</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/02 2:28:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cecpeople.bu.edu/lnalewak/balamini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Our Pets vs Beastlord Warder Questions...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hackersquest.org/boards/viewtopic.php?p=2758#2758">*cough*</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
